  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency response to the people affected by fire in Kitamba locality, Kasai province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project aims to support the most vulnerable people in DRC using the mobile cash transfer modality - who in large proportion have settled unsheltered in public places and in the neighbourhood house accommodates, providing in particular Food, nonfood items( NFI) assistance and emergency locals  shelters  for the most vulnerable people with a special need (Older people, breastfeeding women, pregnant women, non-accompany children, disable people and people with chronic dieses) who are unsheltered. Furthermore, support will be provided in the form of unconditional cash using mobile money transfer to facilitate the affected people buying things on their choice, among the older people and people with disability, while also strengthening their inclusion with regard to the access to health water and sanitation emergency services being established by partners. In addition, due to the WASH needs in the COVID-19 context, this response provide 20 emergency community public toilets, which includes handwashing, soap and sanitation facilities and equipment, using local materials where possible in order to involve the local community in the project and avoid unnecessary movement to reduce COVID-19 transmission.</narrative>
  </description>
